economic anxiety


heightened reception to messages of cultural backlash from populists



populism definition:”Populism is defined as a “thin-centered ideology that considers society to be ultimately separated into two homogeneous and antagonistic groups, ‘the pure people’ versus the ‘corrupt elite,’ and which argues that politics should be an expression of the volonté générale (general will) of the people” (Mudde 2007, p. 23)”

method: literature review
},
